Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: The Problem of White Settlement
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hbd4s
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 7 Dec 1961
African affairs writer and lecturer Margery Perham discusses the effects of colonialism in tropical Africa. In 1939 she became the first female fellow of Nuffield College at Oxford University before being appointed as Director of the Oxford Institute of Colonial Studies in 1945. In her Reith series entitled 'The Colonial Reckoning', she highlights problems of colonial rule. In this lecture entitled 'The Problem of White Settlement', she considers the problem of the European colonists, and the delicate question of race relations. Show less